creator: Henry Lawson
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 15 recordings of The Ships that Won't Go Down by Henry Lawson. This was the Weekly Poetry project for February 16, 2014. Read in English by Algy Pug; Claudia Salto; David Lawrence; Elise C. Boucher; Beth Thomas; fshort; Gayle Cato; Jason Mills; Josh Kirsh; Julia Niedermaier; John Sercel; Kris Moore; Leonard Wilson; TriciaG and Fiddlesticks. Henry Lawson was an Australian writer and poet. Along with his contemporary Banjo Paterson, Lawson is among the best-known Australian poets and fiction writers of the colonial period and is often called Australia's "greatest short story writer". (Summary by Wikipedia ) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
